Chairman, Senate Services Committee and sponsor of the Protection from Internet Falsehoods and Manipulations Bill, Senator Mohammed Sani Musa, All Progressives Congress, APC, Niger East came out on Sunday to defend very strongly, allegations of plagiarism that have been levelled against him. Senator Sani, sponsor of the bill which is described as anti-social media bill, Senator Sani Musa in a Whatsapp message yesterday explained that the similarity between his draft bill and the Singaporean Statute on the same subject was in order. Recall that a copy of the Singaporean legislation on the same subject matter, which surfaced on social media weekend revealed that the title and most of the contents of Musa’s bill currently undergoing debate at the National Assembly were the same.  ABUJA-  THE Senate caucus of Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, yesterday vowed that it would fight against any Bill that would be designed to remove  the rights and freedom of Nigerians that have been guaranteed by the constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. November 12, 2019 In "News" Senator Mohammed Sani Musa, APC, Niger East, is the Chairman, Committee on Senate Services. Penultimate week, Musa re- introduced in the Senate a bill that will regulate the use of the social media in Nigeria, entitled, Protection from Internet Falsehood and Manipulations Bill, 2019 (SB.132)’.In this interview, the bill sponsor… November 24, 2019 In "News" By Henry Umoru - Abuja Again, the Senate has brought back a bill that will regulate the use of social media in Nigeria, this time, entitled, Protection from Internet Falsehood and Manipulations Bill, 2019( SB.132). The Bill which is sponsored by the Chairman, Committee on Senate Services, Senator Mohammed Sani… November 6, 2019 In "News"